3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper deals with the simulation of tile assembly systems, which can involve complex computational processes. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The construction of a universal tile assembly system involves the use of algorithms and data structures to represent and manipulate the supertiles. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The decision-making process involved in expressing the genome of the simulated system T can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem, making this sub-category a possible fit.
